HEADWORD: Contortion
<hw>Con*tor"tion</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧n*t⟦ocir⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>contortio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>contorsion</ets>. See
<er>Contort</er>, and cf. <er>Torsion</er>.]</ety> <def>A twisting; a
writhing; wry motion; a twist; <as>as, the <ex>contortion</ex> of the
muscles of the face</as>.</def> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the <qex>contortions</qex> of the sibyl, without the
inspiration.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contortionist</ent>⟦br⟧
